                    <span>This book is one of the best I've found to learn SQL 7.0 by. Don't let the "Visual Basic" part confuse you. The book is a practical guide on all aspects of SQL 7.0 from installation, database creation, and data manipulation, to the application of the concepts in real-world application examples. The explanations are step-by-step, thorough and very clear so that a novice user can understand fully and quickly become able to create and deploy SQL databases. And once you're ready for more, Vieira's "Professional SQL Server 7.0" is a great follow-up book to this one.</span>
                  
